tags.note: Heacham Park is what remains of the grounds of Heacham Hall, an 18th century house that was destroyed by fire in World War Two. The current Heacham Hall was built in the 80s on the ruins of the kitchen block of the original building. Heacham Park and its

tags.inscription: This garden is close to the site of Walpole Station - part of the Midland and Great Northern Railway. Authorised by Act of Parliament in 1859 it was closed 100 years later in 1959. The A17 now follows the line of the old railway. / The garden was
tags.inscription:2: constructed in remembrance of Eva Kemp 1913 - 2002. / Eva taught at Walpole Cross Keys School for 43 years. / She was a Parish Councillor for 40 years and a District/Borough Councillor for 35 years. / 1991 - 1992 Eva was the Borough Mayor.
